<p>Trying to convert my app to Swift from C++</p>  <p>C++:</p>  <pre><code>static QWORD load64(const OCTET *x) { char i; QWORD u=0;     for(i=7; i&gt;=0; --i) {         u &lt;&lt;= 8;         u |= x[i];     }     return u; } </code></pre>  <p>Swift:</p>  <pre><code>func load64(x: UInt8) -&gt; UInt64 {     var u: UInt64 = 0;     for var i=7; i&gt;=0; --i {         u &lt;&lt;= 8;         u |= x[i];     }     return u; } </code></pre>  <p>But this line doesnt work in Swift:</p>  <pre><code>u |= x[i]; </code></pre>  <p>And I can't seem to find any reference to selecting a specific bit from an integer... anyone know how?</p>